abstract: Chinese officials said growth in the second quarter was just 6.2 percent, showing the limits of Beijing’s ability to juice its economy.
snippet: Chinese officials said growth in the second quarter was just 6.2 percent, showing the limits of Beijing’s ability to juice its economy.

abstract: A series of coordinated deportation raids is targeting recently arrived families from Central America.
snippet: A series of coordinated deportation raids is targeting recently arrived families from Central America.
lead_paragraph: A small number of coordinated federal raids targeting undocumented migrant parents and their children took place over the weekend, the beginning of the Trump administration’s plan to swiftly enforce deportation orders against some 2,000 recently arrived migrants who are not eligible to remain in the country.

abstract: The failure affected 73,000 customers, trapping people in subways and elevators for a time and eerily dimming the lights in a swath of Times Square.
snippet: The failure affected 73,000 customers, trapping people in subways and elevators for a time and eerily dimming the lights in a swath of Times Square.
lead_paragraph: [Update: Con Edison apologized for the power outage, but offered few clues about the root cause.]

abstract: New York’s “back yard” has long been known for free outdoor performances. OZY Fest is a break with that tradition.
snippet: New York’s “back yard” has long been known for free outdoor performances. OZY Fest is a break with that tradition.
lead_paragraph: The Great Lawn in Central Park has been the setting for some of the most iconic outdoor performances in New York City, from Simon and Garfunkel to Diana Ross, from Elton John to James Taylor.

abstract: The Epstein case is a reminder of the depraved milieu from which our president sprang.
snippet: The Epstein case is a reminder of the depraved milieu from which our president sprang.
lead_paragraph: On Monday, Donald Trump disinvited the then-British ambassador, Kim Darroch, from an official administration dinner with the emir of Qatar, because he was mad about leaked cables in which Darroch assessed the president as “insecure” and “incompetent.”

abstract: The purchase of the sophisticated S-400 antiaircraft equipment was fiercely opposed by NATO and by Washington, which is expected to respond with sanctions.
snippet: The purchase of the sophisticated S-400 antiaircraft equipment was fiercely opposed by NATO and by Washington, which is expected to respond with sanctions.
lead_paragraph: ISTANBUL — Defying strenuous American objections and the threat of sanctions, Turkey began receiving the first shipment of a sophisticated Russian surface-to-air missile system on Friday, a step certain to test the country’s uneasy place in the NATO alliance.

headline_main: Turkey Gets Shipment of Russian Missile System, Defying U.S.
headline_print_headline: Defying U.S., Turkey Receives Part of Russian Missile System

abstract: The Gulf Coast is being inundated with rain and preparing for possible landfall of a tropical storm. A study of recent hurricanes found that climate change increased rainfall by up to 9 percent.
snippet: The Gulf Coast is being inundated with rain and preparing for possible landfall of a tropical storm. A study of recent hurricanes found that climate change increased rainfall by up to 9 percent.
lead_paragraph: When a tropical storm is approaching, its intensity or wind speed often gets the bulk of the attention. But as Tropical Storm Barry bears down on the Gulf Coast in the coming days, it’s the water that the storm will bring with it that has weather watchers worried.

abstract: Amazon’s effort could help answer a fundamental question: Will automation be a solution for the great challenges of the 21st century economy, or make those problems worse?
snippet: Amazon’s effort could help answer a fundamental question: Will automation be a solution for the great challenges of the 21st century economy, or make those problems worse?
lead_paragraph: As automation technology has leapt ahead, workers increasingly worry about losing their jobs to robots and algorithms. Economists dismiss those concerns, by and large, arguing that workers can grab higher-skilled jobs with better wages.
